elf": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126/comments/125266834.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126/_/diff#comment-125266834"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 3126, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126"}}, "title": "Fixes for finding OGRE with CMake config files"}, "content": {"raw": "If I can provide any help in getting this merged \\(for example reviewing other Gazebo PRs in queue\\) feel free to let me know, thanks!", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>If I can provide any help in getting this merged (for example reviewing other Gazebo PRs in queue) feel free to let me know, thanks!</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-11-18T20:22:43.286871+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Silvio Traversaro", "uuid": "{34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6/578caaa1-056c-45a2-8bf9-bee94c3bebef/128"}}, "nickname": "traversaro", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6"}, "updated_on": "2019-11-18T20:22:43.624831+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 125266834}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 3126, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126"}}, "title": "Fixes for finding OGRE with CMake config files"}}, {"comment": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126/comments/116926667.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126/_/diff#comment-116926667"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 3126, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126"}}, "title": "Fixes for finding OGRE with CMake config files"}, "content": {"raw": "cc @{5bee878f5416561374c46bd9}", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>cc <span class=\"ap-mention\" data-atlassian-id=\"5bee878f5416561374c46bd9\">@Sean Yen</span></p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2019-09-15T21:09:07.876526+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Silvio Traversaro", "uuid": "{34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B34f404cb-5642-4f27-a032-e04c7143d776%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6/578caaa1-056c-45a2-8bf9-bee94c3bebef/128"}}, "nickname": "traversaro", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:e1c3e6a0-9a64-4e5f-a668-feebc191c5b6"}, "updated_on": "2019-09-15T21:10:38.866867+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 116926667}, "pull_request": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 3126, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/pullrequests/3126.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/3126"}}, "title": "Fixes for finding OGRE with CMake config files"}}, {"update": {"description": "Back in  [#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2692](#!/osrf/gazebo/pull-requests/2692), I added this part of  CMake code to find OGRE in systems without pkg-config. However, back in time I probably tested these changes with a modified OGRE, as  there are some problems in the current version that  prevent to configure Gazebo successfully with OGRE if `pkg-config` is not available. This PR fixes this problems. \r\n\r\nIn particular, the fixed problems are: \r\n\r\n* There is a nasty bug in CMake \\(see [https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/issues/17135](https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/issues/17135)\\) that  prevents to successfully run a `find_package(<package>)` call if before there was a failed call to `pkg_check_modules(<package> <package>)` . You  can find the details in [https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/issues/17135#note\\_626879](https://gitlab.kitware.com/cmake/cmake/issues/17135#note_626879) , but a workaround is to manually unset the `OGRE_FOUND` cache variable.\r\n* The `OGRE_PLUGINDIR` is used  in the main Gazebo CMakeLists.txt \\(see [#!/osrf/gazebo/src/7c4281fe1229236496a0532515d596dbb4c86e70/CMakeLists.txt#lines-164](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/7c4281fe1229236496a0532515d596dbb4c86e70/CMakeLists.txt#lines-164)\\), but OGRE\u2019s just exports `OGRE_PLUGIN_DIR` . To  be  compatible with the `pkg-config` related code, we just assign to `OGRE_PLUGINDIR` the value  of `OGRE_PLUGIN_DIR` . \r\n\r\n\u200c\r\n\r\nDownstream related PR: [https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg/pull/8178](https://github.com/microsoft/vcpkg/pull/8178) .\r\n\r\n\u200c", "title": "Fixes for finding OGRE with CMake config files", "destination": {"commit": {"hash": "7c4281fe1229", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/commit/7c4281fe1229.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/commits/7c4281fe1229"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "branch": {"name": "gazebo10"}}, "reason": "", "source": {"commit": {"hash": "192200de98d2", "type": "commit", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/traversaro/gazebo-20/commit/192200de98d2"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/traversaro/gazebo-20/commits/192200de98d2"}}}, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "https://